displayName.text: New York City Human Resources Administration - Dyckman Job Center

adrFormatAddress: 4055 10th Ave, New York, NY 10034-1147, USA

originalText.text: Went to get a new Fair Fares card.  The security staff was so nice and helpful.  They guided me to the Check-in kiosk and told me which buttons to press. Once I got my print out of my waiting number they guided me to the lower level where the Fair Fares office was.  The staff was nice and attentive.  I was done in 10 minutes since I was the only one there.  This was around 1pm on a Wednesday.

originalText.text:
I am moving Upstate, NY so I had to go there, & tell them my new address as for my health insurance. The Security Officer's there are so kind, & respectful. The two women who helped me with the health insurance were the exact same. Very kind, & respectful. It didn't take too long either. I would guess about a half an hour. Pretty good.
Thank you for your help, & kindness.

originalText.text: They made a mistake on my ESNA form regarding the amount. Their staff made the mistake and when I called the number to address the error, they told me i had to come into the office to have it corrected, which is ridiculous. Why are you making people fix the mistakes your staff make, this is just really bad organization. Worse experience ever and anxiety is not worth the incompetence of your staff getting stuff  wrong on my documents.
